## Summary

Live in ~/.clawq/daemon.log (2026-05-21 14:57 – 15:55): four separate teams
session turns failed with:

  Failure(\"LLM API error (HTTP 404): <html>...nginx...</html>\")

Each preceded by a successful-looking dispatch:
  -> LLM provider=minimax model=MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed msgs=141..144 ~44k tok
  MiniMax stream request to https://api.minimax.io/anthropic/v1/messages model=MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed

All 3 retries fail (404 returns immediately), then the user sees an error.
Model name is correctly normalized via `api_model_name` (provider_minimax.ml
line 5-14) so this is not a casing issue.

Each affected turn was at message count >140 (long context).

## Hypotheses

1. MiniMax's nginx fronts the Anthropic-compat endpoint and returns 404 when
   the request body is too large or fails internal validation BEFORE the
   real model sees it.
2. Rate limiting via 404 (unusual but possible).
3. A path issue when streaming is enabled (we hit the *streaming* endpoint
   for the broken requests).

## Suggested next steps

1. When HTTP 404 is returned by a known-good base URL, log the request body
   size and the response Content-Length / response headers to disk for
   inspection.
2. Add a single-retry-with-non-streaming fallback: if stream attempt 404s,
   try the same body via `complete` (non-streaming). This may bypass an
   nginx-level streaming guard.
3. Add a regression: a mock SSE server that returns 404 should not cause the
   3-retry storm — it should be surfaced quickly with a clear user-facing
   error.

